E4Plus1.uk.description: Lisa Gets the Blues: Lisa gets the yips and Bart is made to dress up and sing as Annie from the musical. They go to New Orleans to recover. (S29 Ep17/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: A Springfield Summer Christmas for Christmas: A cable channel films a Christmas movie in Springfield, and Skinner falls in love. (S32 Ep10)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Manger Things: A secret from Flanders' past is revealed, and we discover a room in the Simpsons' home that we've never seen before. (S32 Ep16)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Movie
E4Plus1.uk.description: (2007) Animated comedy. When Homer's love for a pig causes world-threatening pollution, Springfield gets enclosed in a huge dome. D'oh! Will he do the decent thing and save his neighbours?

E4Plus1.uk.title: New: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series - Bart's Birthday: Bart has to organise his own birthday party when Homer forgets to post the invitations. Mr Burns fakes his own death. (S36 Ep1/18)

E4Plus1.uk.title: New: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series - The Yellow Lotus: The Simpsons stumble across a mystery and an old enemy while they're on holiday at a peculiar island resort. Dr Hibbert drugs an otter. (S36 Ep2/18)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Free Guy
E4Plus1.uk.description: (2021) Comedy action starring Ryan Reynolds. Guy lives in Free City. Free City isn't real. Nor is Guy. It's all a big online game. Can he take down the corrupt game publisher?

Film4.uk.title: The Equalizer
Film4.uk.description: (2014) Thriller. Denzel Washington stars as an ex-soldier who comes out of retirement to help a teenage sex worker who's been assaulted by her pimp.

Film4.uk.title: Three Billboards Outside...
Film4.uk.description: ...Ebbing, Missouri: (2017) Oscar-winning dark comedy about a mother who wants the cops to solve her daughter's murder using three precisely worded billboards. Starring Frances McDormand.

Film4.uk.title: Wish You Were Here
Film4.uk.description: (1987) Award-winning comedy-drama set in an English seaside town in the early 1950s. Emily Lloyd stars as a spirited teenager whose sexual awakening comes at a price. With Tom Bell.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: The Lavender Hill Mob
Film4.uk.description: (1951) Classic Ealing comedy starring Alec Guinness as a mild-mannered bank clerk who assembles a gang to hijack a million quid's worth of gold. Which is when their problems really start...

Film4.uk.title: Mr Popper's Penguins
Film4.uk.description: (2011) Family comedy. Jim Carrey stars as a work-obsessed New York property developer whose life is turned upside down when he receives a crate containing six live penguins.

Film4.uk.title: Deck the Halls
Film4.uk.description: (2006) Comedy. Neighbours Matthew Broderick and Danny DeVito get extremely competitive as they festoon their houses with increasingly outrageous festive decorations and lights.

Film4.uk.title: Sleepless in Seattle
Film4.uk.description: (1993) Romantic comedy with Tom Hanks and Meg Ryan. A bereaved man gets another chance at love when his son puts him on a radio talk show.

Film4.uk.title: Moonfall
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Sci-fi disaster with Halle Berry. A NASA bigwig, a disgraced astronaut and a conspiracy theorist are all that stand between the Earth and a plummeting Moon. But are aliens involved?

Film4.uk.title: Mission: Impossible - Dead...
Film4.uk.description: ...Reckoning: (2023) Tom Cruise returns as Ethan Hunt and jumps a motorbike off a mountain for real. There's some stuff about an all-powerful AI. But it's the thrills that we're here for!

Film4.uk.title: Scarface
Film4.uk.description: (1983) Al Pacino stars in Brian De Palma's classic crime thriller. A Cuban immigrant uses the cocaine trade to take what he wants of the American dream. Say hello to my little friend.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Little Women
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Greta Gerwig's Oscar-winning period drama adaptation of the classic Louisa May Alcott novel, starring Emma Watson, Saoirse Ronan, Florence Pugh, Timothe Chalamet and Meryl Streep.

Film4.uk.title: Romancing the Stone
Film4.uk.description: (1984) Comedy action adventure starring Michael Douglas and Kathleen Turner. An adventurer helps a bestselling author to search for her sister, who's been kidnapped in Colombia.

Film4.uk.title: Tora! Tora! Tora!
Film4.uk.description: (1970) Oscar-winning drama portraying the bombing of Pearl Harbor, from both American and Japanese perspectives. With Joseph Cotten and So Yamamura.

Film4.uk.title: Hunter Killer
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Nautical action thriller. Gerard Butler stars as an unconventional submarine skipper sent to investigate the torpedoing of a US vessel. With Gary Oldman, Linda Cardellini and Common.

Film4.uk.title: Plane
Film4.uk.description: (2023) Action thriller starring Gerard Butler as an airline pilot who must become a one-man army after crashlanding on an island overrun by bad guys. To survive, he's gonna have to wing it.

Film4.uk.title: Late Night with the Devil
Film4.uk.description: (2023) Unsettling found-footage horror with David Dastmalchian. A has-been host tries to save his 70s talk show using a demonically possessed 13-year-old girl. Really, what could go wrong?

Film4.uk.title: Carlito's Way
Film4.uk.description: (1993) Brian De Palma's crime thriller with Al Pacino. An ex-con, fresh out of jail, flamboyantly declares his plan to go straight. But his criminal past just won't let him go...

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Muppets from Space
Film4.uk.description: (1999) The Muppets are back in another feature-length adventure as Gonzo, convinced that he is of alien origin, struggles to communicate with his family in outer space.

Film4.uk.title: Tooth Fairy
Film4.uk.description: (2010) Family fantasy comedy. Dwayne Johnson stars as a tough ice hockey player who is transformed into a real-life fairy as punishment for telling a child that tooth fairies don't exist.

Film4.uk.title: My Spy
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Family action comedy. A CIA agent (Dave Bautista) gets the run-around from a nine-year-old girl when he's sent to keep an eye on her family. With Chloe Coleman.

Film4.uk.title: One Million Years B.C.
Film4.uk.description: (1966) Raquel Welch - in her famous fur bikini - stars in this prehistoric adventure set in an inhospitable landscape populated by two warring tribes and Ray Harryhausen's roving dinosaurs.

Film4.uk.title: The League of Extraordinary...
Film4.uk.description: ...Gentlemen: (2003) Fantasy with Sean Connery. In an alternative Victorian age, can Allan Quatermain, Dorian Gray, Captain Nemo, Mina Harker and the Invisible Man avert a war?

Film4.uk.title: The Banshees of Inisherin
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Colin Farrell and Brendan Gleeson star in writer and director Martin McDonagh's award-winning tragicomedy about the end of a life-long friendship on a very small island. Awkward.

Film4.uk.title: The Hunt
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Fighty, satirical horror that upset Donald Trump. Hilary Swank plays a rich lefty who likes hunting working class people to the death. But she didn't reckon on Betty Gilpin.

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The Main Line Experience: Fred Dibnah visits Llangollen Railway, where he reminisces about the past, and is given a chance to fulfil a childhood dream with driver Robert Haslam. S1 Ep10

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Bluebell Railway: Fred Dibnah visits the Bluebell Railway in East Sussex. His first footplate ride of the day is on Fenchurch, where he is pleasantly surprised to meet a fire lady. S1 Ep11

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Railway Yards and Workshops: Fred Dibnah explains what happens in railway works, visiting Bo'ness and Kinneil, Scotland, and the Boston Lodge in Ffestiniog, Wales. S1 Ep12

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Midland Railway: Fred Dibnah visits the Midland Railway Centre in Derbyshire, is given a tour of the sheds and gets to have a go on the hydraulic riveter. S1 Ep13

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Severn Valley Railway: Fred Dibnah drives his own engine to Bridgnorth, Shropshire, to see an engine repair shed and purpose-built boiler shop. S1 Ep14

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Great Central Railway: Fred visits the Great Central Railway, the only remaining main line railway in the country which still has steam locomotives, where he takes a footplate ride. S1 Ep15

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Introduction: David Attenborough catalogues life beneath the ocean waves. All manner of spectacular lifeforms dwell deep underwater, from alien monsters to pack-hunting killer whales. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The Deep: The mysteries of the oceans are revealed in this stunning series narrated by David Attenborough. Among the oddities featured here are terrifying fish with massive teeth. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Open Ocean: Oceanic explorations, topped off with David Attenborough's masterful narration. Learn about the predatory skills of some of the planet's most charismatic hunters. S1 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Frozen Seas: David Attenborough salutes the survival techniques of creatures who endure harsh conditions in the Arctic and Antarctic, as the lauded natural history series continues. S1 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Seasonal Seas: David Attenborough vividly describes the history of our oceans. Seasonal changes in the richest waters on Earth drive an explosion of life, from seals to jellyfish. S1 Ep5

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
